  • Constructor Details

    • Pharmacist

      public Pharmacist(String Name, Date DOB, Boolean Gender)
      Constructs a Pharmacist object with the specified name, date of birth, and gender. The ID is automatically assigned based on the current value of lastID, which is then incremented. The role is set to ROLE.PHARMACIST.
      Parameters:
      Name - The name of the pharmacist.
      DOB - The date of birth of the pharmacist.
      Gender - The gender of the pharmacist. True for male, False for female.

    • Pharmacist

      public Pharmacist(int ID, String Name, Date DOB, Boolean Gender)
      Constructs a Pharmacist object with the specified ID, name, date of birth, and gender. This constructor is used for initializing a Pharmacist object from a saved record in the text file HMS.txt. The role is set to ROLE.PHARMACIST.
      Parameters:
      ID - The unique identifier for the pharmacist.
      Name - The name of the pharmacist.
      DOB - The date of birth of the pharmacist.
      Gender - The gender of the pharmacist. True for male, False for female.
